name: pitstop
description: This repo contains a sample application based on a Garage Management System for Pitstop - a fictitious garage. The primary goal of this sample is to demonstrate several software-architecture concepts like: Microservices, CQRS, Event Sourcing, Domain Driven Design (DDD), Eventual Consistency.

name: inventory-management-system-microservice
description: A scalable microservices application built with Node.js, Prisma, MongoDB, Redis, RabbitMQ, Kong, and Docker. Designed for high performance, reliability, and streamlined deployments.

name: OwnLightSystem
description: OwnLightSystem is an academic project that develops a scalable, microservices-based smart lighting control system for smart homes. It offers device management, secure authentication, automation routines, and energy monitoring, built with technologies such as .NET, PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Ocelot API Gateway, and Docker.

name: OrderNotificationSystem
description: OrderNotificationSystem is an microservice. In this there are two service called orderService and notificationService and they communicate through ActiveMQ

name: fleet-management-system
description: This is a reference for building Java microservices and deploying them across various environments, such as Docker, Kubernetes, and AWS

name: QuizApp-Microservices
description: This application is a microservices-based system that manages quizzes and questions. It features separate services for handling quiz creation, question management, and score calculation, all accessed through an API Gateway for seamless routing and communication.

name: RoleAssignmentsSystem
description: A microservices-based system for managing users and roles, built with Java 17 and Spring Boot. Features secure authentication with Spring Security, event-driven architecture with Kafka, and containerized deployment via Docker.

name: logistics
description: A Scalable microservices-based system using Go for efficient logistics operations with real-time location tracking.

name: auth-master
description: The project is a distributed system based on microservice architecture designed to manage users and their roles.

name: Order-MealMate
description: Order-MealMate service manages customer orders in the MealMate system, handling order creation, updates, and tracking in a microservices architecture.

name: Stack-OverFlow-2.0
description: This project is a basic implementation of a Stack Overflow-like system built first as a monolithic web-based application and later broken down into microservices. The main goal of this project is to demonstrate the transition from a monolithic architecture to a microservices architecture.

name: BIS2_satellite-tasking
description: Microservice for a Recommender System that handles satellite tasking, processes tasking recommendations, and retrieves imagery from Landsat, Sentinel, and MODIS via Microsoft Planetary Computer. Developed with Flask for the Business Information Systems 2 course at Politecnico di Milano in collaboration with eGeos and Cherrydata.

name: Distributed-Quotation-Services-RMI
description: This project demonstrates a multi-module distributed system built using Java RMI, Docker, and Maven. The system includes multiple quotation services, a broker, and a client, all containerized using Docker. Managed via Docker Compose, each service operates in isolation, showcasing the use of microservices architecture in distributed environments.

name: zeeshansyeddev
description: I have 3+ years experience in WordPress design & SEO as a Freelancer on different freelance websites. Studying Cloud Native AI Engineering @ PIAIC Skilled in Python, Docker, VS Code Building Custom GPTs & AI Systems Exploring Humanoid Robotics Passionate about Generative AI, Microservices, Automation

name: CapstoneProject
description: This capstone project, Human Resource Management System (HRMS), was developed for the completion of a Master’s degree in IT at University of the People. It streamlines HR tasks like recruitment, performance, and attendance tracking, using microservices architecture and cloud-based deployment for efficient, scalable, and secure workforce management
